# API route prefix convention (V0.6.5+)

Every new HTTP surface added to this repo MUST live under exactly one of the top-level prefixes below. The audience determines the prefix; pick the prefix first, design the handler second.

| Prefix                          | Audience                                              | Auth                                                                                                      | Examples                                                                                       |
| ------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `/api/v1/admin/**`              | System administrators                                 | `current_admin_user` FastAPI dependency (session-cookie based). Long-lived admin tokens deferred.         | `/api/v1/admin/words`, `/api/v1/admin/packs`, `/api/v1/admin/global-packs`, `/api/v1/admin/cron` |
| `/api/v1/public/**`             | Anonymous (any caller)                                | None. Vercel deployment-protection still gates preview deploys; production is fully public.              | `/api/v1/public/health`, `/api/v1/public/packs/latest.json`, `/api/v1/public/global-packs/latest.json`, future AB-flag manifests |
| `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/**` | Members of one family (parents + bound child devices) | Per-family auth (parent session OR child Bearer device-token belonging to `family_id`). Auth deferred until later version; for now, accept the path param as decorative. | `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/family-packs`, `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/inbox`, `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/account` |
| `/v1/oauth/{provider}/**`       | Pre-login parent (browser redirect OAuth)             | None on `start`; `callback` exchanges IdP code on **canonical production host**; `finish` redeems a one-time handoff ticket. Issues parent `wm_session` when complete. | `/v1/oauth/google/start`, `/v1/oauth/google/callback`, `/v1/oauth/google/finish`; future `/v1/oauth/apple/*`, `/v1/oauth/wechat/*`, `/v1/oauth/alipay/*` |

**Note:** `/v1/oauth/**` is intentionally **not** under `/api/v1/...`. It is a site-root OAuth redirect namespace (browser flows, not JSON family APIs). Do **not** nest OAuth under `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/auth/oauth/...`.

## Rule of thumb

1. If the resource is per-family or per-device-bound → `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/...`
2. Else, if it requires admin context (cross-tenant management, system content authoring) → `/api/v1/admin/...`
3. Else, if it is anonymous-readable platform content → `/api/v1/public/...`
4. Else, if it is a **pre-login third-party OAuth redirect** (Google / Apple / WeChat / Alipay) → `/v1/oauth/{provider}/...` (see § Pre-login parent OAuth below)
5. Otherwise, **stop and discuss** — you probably haven't named the audience precisely.

## Web (HTML) pages mirror the same pattern

- `/admin/**` — system admin web shells (e.g. global-pack authoring UI in v0.6.6+).
- `/public/**` — anonymous landing pages (e.g. preview-urls dashboards).
- `/family/{family_id}/**` — parent web shell scoped to a family (pre-login HTML entry: **`/family/login`**; decorative `_` remains on pre-login **`/family/_/auth/*`** form posts and JSON **`/api/v1/family/_/auth/*`** until a session exists).

## Historical legacy URLs (removed)

Older docs and clients referred to `/api/v1/parent/**`, `/api/v1/child/**`, bare `/api/v1/health`, `/api/v1/packs/latest.json`, `/api/v1/preview-urls.json`, `/api/v1/auth/**` (admin), `/api/v1/pair/redeem`, and `/parent/**`. Those entrypoints are **not served anymore**; use the `admin`, `public`, `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/**`, `/v1/oauth/{provider}/**`, and `/family/{family_id}/**` prefixes above. Do **not** add `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/auth/oauth/**` — OAuth uses `/v1/oauth/` only. When you touch routing, update `docs/WordMagicGame_overall_spec.md` section 13 (route table + prefix convention) in the same change.

## Pre-login parent OTP

Parent email OTP JSON endpoints and sibling HTML forms live at `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/auth/*` and `/family/{family_id}/auth/*`. Until a session exists, callers use a decorative `family_id` such as `_` on those auth paths (see apex `/` → **`/family/login`** in `server/app/main.py`).

## Pre-login parent OAuth (V0.6.8+)

Third-party login uses **`/v1/oauth/{provider}/start|callback|finish`** (not under decorative `family_id`).

| Step | Path | Host | Purpose |
| ---- | ---- | ---- | ------- |
| Start | `/v1/oauth/{provider}/start` | Any deployment | Signed `state` + optional `return_origin`; 302 to IdP |
| Callback | `/v1/oauth/{provider}/callback` | **Canonical production only** (`OAUTH_CANONICAL_BASE_URL`, default `https://happyword.cool`) | Exchange code, verify `id_token`, merge/link `oauth_identities`, issue session **or** handoff ticket |
| Finish | `/v1/oauth/{provider}/finish` | Deployment matching signed `return_origin` | Redeem one-time ticket → `set_parent_session_cookie` on that host |

**Providers (path segment):** `google`, `apple`, `wechat`, `alipay` — add new providers only under `/v1/oauth/<name>/...`.

**Google Console redirect URI (production):** register exactly one callback per provider, e.g. `https://happyword.cool/v1/oauth/google/callback`. Do not register per-preview URLs.

**Vercel Preview:** use the production callback + signed `return_origin` allowlist (`GET /api/v1/public/preview-urls.json` + `*.vercel.app` + local dev origins). After callback on production, redirect to `{return_origin}/v1/oauth/{provider}/finish?ticket=...` — never rely on cross-domain cookies between `happyword.cool` and `*.vercel.app`.

**Login UI:** `/family/login` keeps email OTP in parallel; OAuth buttons link to `start` (preview/local may use absolute `https://happyword.cool/v1/oauth/.../start?return_origin=...`).

**Design reference:** [`docs/superpowers/specs/2026-05-16-parent-oauth-login-design.md`](docs/superpowers/specs/2026-05-16-parent-oauth-login-design.md).

## Enforcement

When adding a new `APIRouter(prefix=...)` line:

- JSON/API routers: prefix MUST start with `/api/v1/admin`, `/api/v1/public`, or `/api/v1/family`.
- OAuth redirect routers: prefix MUST be `/v1/oauth/<provider>` (one router file per provider or a shared factory — do not use `/api/v1/family/.../oauth/...`).
- HTML routers: `/admin`, `/public`, or `/family` (unchanged).
- Do not resurrect removed legacy prefixes for new work.
- Update [docs/WordMagicGame_overall_spec.md](docs/WordMagicGame_overall_spec.md) §13.3 (route table) and §13.7 (route prefix convention) in the same PR that adds or changes routes.

## When this rule does NOT apply

- Static asset paths served by Vercel (e.g. `/_next/...`, `/favicon.ico`).
- Vercel cron entrypoints under `/api/v1/admin/cron/*` already follow the rule.
- Internal `/__mock_state__/*` debug endpoints in `server/mock_ui_server.py` (test fixture only, not a production surface).
